  "event_preview": "Dover Motor Speedway is a 1.0-mile (1.609 km) concrete oval in Dover, Delaware, with 24-degree banking in the turns and 9-degree banking on the straightaways — a high-grip surface that produces some of the fastest short-track lap times in NASCAR and places extreme demands on brakes, tyres and mechanical grip across a full distance. The 42nd NASCAR All-Star Race makes Dover the sixth venue to host the exhibition event, following Charlotte, North Wilkesboro, Texas, Atlanta and Bristol. After three consecutive years at North Wilkesboro, the $1 million prize moves to the Monster Mile.\n\nThe race spans 350 laps across three segments: two opening 75-lap heats with a full 36-car field, followed by a 200-lap finale restricted to 26 drivers, determined by best average finish across the first two segments. Nineteen drivers are already locked into the finale — the 17 Cup race winners from 2025 and 2026 plus two past All-Star Race winners competing full-time — leaving six spots to be earned on track and one for the Fan Vote winner. Defending All-Star Race winner Christopher Bell is locked in automatically, while Kyle Larson's three All-Star victories are the most of any active driver. Denny Hamlin is the most recent points-race winner at Dover, having taken victory there in double overtime in July 2025.",
